If MSS. are right in premit, the words most naturally mean ‘Jupiter keeps the fires down and only working in secret‚' i. e. keeps the volcanic forces as much to the inside of the mountain as he can; outside their effects are permanently visible in boulders and sand. This, however, after the de- tailed description in 198-201 of burning masses of rock heaved into the air, thunder-like detonations‚ and livid flames, is all but impossible: the contrast of in occulto with the visible and tremendous phenomena of eruption would be too pro- nounced.
